text: Ulrica Schenström Ulrica Schenström (born 1972) is a Swedish politician and a member of the Moderate Party. She was Secretary of state to the Prime Minister in the Cabinet of Fredrik Reinfeldt (2006–2007). She resigned from her position after she was photographed in a restaurant embracing and kissing a political journalist from TV4."Reinfeldt: Schenström was on call", The Local, Nov 1, 2007 ==References== Category:1972 births Category:Living people Category:Moderate Party politicians Category:Swedish women in politics Category:21st-century Swedish women politicians
